# Ktor Server Package Structure

Server module layout under application package:

```
Application.kt
config/
di/
plugins/
routes/
services/
data/tables/
data/dao/
util/
models/ (optional, prefer shared module for KMP DTOs)
```

Rules:

- Keep `Application.kt` as wiring only.
- Install DI first, initialize database, then call `configure*()` plugins in explicit order.
- Put plugin setup in `plugins/` (`configureSerialization`, `configureStatusPages`, `configureMonitoring`, `configureRouting`, `configureBackgroundJobs`, etc.).
- Put route groups in `routes/` with `fun Route.xxxRoutes()`.
- Keep handlers thin: parse/validate input, call service, respond.
- Keep business logic in `services/` (constructor injection only, no framework dependencies).
- Keep table definitions in `data/tables/`, queries in `data/dao/`.
- Keep shared API DTOs in `shared` module for KMP projects.
